text.tspan: Yes You became a slave for me.
What kind of love You have for man,
My nature, Lord, is just sin.
All that You are was condemning me.
What made You Lord to die for me?
You joined manâ€™s race and took my place,
Your blood is flowing now for me.
O, what a price You paid for us!
No tongue or pen can ever tell:
Your mercy reached me down in hell.
